      "updatedAt": "2026-04-19T04:58:22.359Z",
      "body": "`plan/` is the mutable working surface for active work.\n\nIf a file answers \"what are we doing right now?\", \"what did we find?\", or \"what did we decide while working?\" it probably belongs closer to plan than memory. The point is to externalize reasoning into files so work can continue across turns and across agents.\n\nThis is why brief / roadmap / state / codebase / phase artifacts belong here: plan is the workspace, not the archive.\n\nA useful pattern from the discussion was:\n\n- tasks / progress\n- findings / notes\n- decisions / log\n\nThat is the shape of working memory before anything gets promoted into longer-lived memory or knowledge.",
